  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      It has been shown that N-methyl-D-aspartate (NMDA) receptor antagonists (such as ketamine)
      potentiate analgesic drug's efficacy. Polyamines are allosteric modulators of NMDA receptors.
      In animal studies, polyamine-free diet has shown antinociceptive properties. This research
      aims at evaluating analgesic properties of polyamine-low diet after laparoscopic
      cholecystectomy performed in an ambulatory setting.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
